@article{Makki_2018,
abstract = {Multi-tenant Software-as-a-Service (SaaS) applications share a single runtime instance among multiple customer organizations (tenants). To account for differences in tenant requirements, they have to support run-time customization. Run-time customization involves a wide range of software artifacts such as user interfaces, databases, web-services and business process or workflow definitions. This paper analyzes and compares the quality implications of different business process customization strategies for multi-tenant SaaS applications. The customization strategies are selected from an existing survey and the comparison criteria are derived from two essential characteristics of SaaS: it is (i) a business model aiming at â€œeconomies of scaleâ€ and (ii) a software delivery model with specific automation requirements. The comparative study shows that there is no single best strategy, and provides SaaS architects with support for making appropriate trade-off decisions when adopting a workflow customization strategy. As a by-product of this study, a number of points for future improvement and innovations in existing workflow technology are identified, which are exclusively relevant for multi-tenant SaaS applications.},
